    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it doesn't feel like a \"period\" of something. it feels permanent. like the spark just died for good. i try to pick up a brush or sit at the piano and it's just... noise. it's mechanical. i'm just going through the motions of being a human, but the \"me\" part—the part that actually cares, the part that creates—is gone. i feel like an actor playing a role in a life i dont even want anymore. what's the point of keeping the machine running if the soul is already gone?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
