      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Hearing you describe this pain this way is heartbreaking, and it is completely understandable that you feel hopeless when treatment feels like force-feeding a hopeless situation. While medical tools are designed to help, they cannot replace the personal connection and genuine safety that makes you feel heard and valued again. You deserve to be treated with enough compassion and time for your pain to be respected, even if the \"music\" isn't there yet. If you feel hopeless again, please call or text 988 immediately—they hear pain like yours every day and are dedicated to walking with you through the darkest moments.",
